Female (
Figs. 6G, H
; 
9B, D
; 
10C
):

Larger than male (
Fig. 10C
). Most morphological structures as in males. Maxillary palps light green. Pronotum surface smooth. Spatula-like forewings (
Fig. 9F
), the right with one almost straight line of conical stridulatory teeth, as large as long, the line curving ca. 50º and forming a F-like vein with several longer teeth (
Fig. 9D
). Lateral lobes of pronotum with a plain light band, from anterior to posterior edge; tricolor band absent. Abdomen greenish with a lateral white band. Tergite X at least half as long as IX; posterior edge undulated with a median depression; without any protuberance. Conical cerci, as long as epiproct. Subgenital plate triangular with obtuse apex; its base at least four times as wide as apex (
Fig. 6G
). Ovipositor twice as long as pronotum, almost straight; acuminate; serrulations from the distal fourth of dorsal valves and in the distal fifth of inferior valves (
Fig. 6H
). This description corresponds to the 
paratype
listed below.
